  "bio": [
    "Mariarosa Lavelli is the widow of Giuseppe Crippa (d. 2025), the late founder of Technoprobe, an Italian manufacturer of probe cards, small devices that test the functionality of microchips.",
    "Crippa founded Technoprobe in 1989 in his garage and attic alongside his son Cristiano; Lavelli provided administrative help.",
    "Technoprobe went public on Euronext Milan in 2022; Lavelli owns an 11% stake."
